---
import { Image } from "astro:assets";
import Layout from "@/layouts/Project.astro";
import Heading from "@/components/ui/Heading.astro";
import Text from "@/components/ui/Text.astro";
import ProjectContnetWrapper from "@/components/ui/ProjectContnetWrapper.astro";
import SwiperSlider from "@/components/ui/SwiperSlider.astro";
import { loadImages } from "@/utils/loadImages";
import logo from "@/assets/logo/fwlogo-min.png";
import moodboardImg from "@/assets/fillwiseProcess/moodboard.png";
import onboarding1Img from "@/assets/fillwiseProcess/onboarding-1.png";
import onboarding2Img from "@/assets/fillwiseProcess/onboarding-2.png";
import landingImg from "@/assets/fillwiseProcess/landing.png";

const title = "FillWise.ai";
const years = "Side Project 2025";
const description = "AI-powered Chrome extension for intelligent form filling";

const imageModules = import.meta.glob<{ default: ImageMetadata }>(
  "/src/assets/fillwise/*.{jpeg,jpg,png,gif}"
);

const sliderImages = await loadImages(imageModules);
---

<Layout {title} {years} {description} {logo}>
  <ProjectContnetWrapper>
    <Heading level={2} size="xl" weight="semibold">Problem Statement</Heading>
    <Text class="mb-[1.562rem]"
      >Professionals across HR, travel management, and sales face repetitive
      data entry tasks when transferring information from CRM systems,
      documents, or physical forms into web interfaces - a process that consumes
      significant time and introduces human error.</Text
    >
    <Heading level={2} size="xl" weight="semibold">How It Started</Heading>
    <Text class="mb-[1.562rem]"
      >I built FillWise for my wife. The tools I found felt inconvenient: they
      filled forms with random data or asked you to map every field by
      hand.</Text
    >
    <Heading level={2} size="xl" weight="semibold">Solution</Heading>
    <Text class="mb-[1.562rem]"
      >Developed an intelligent Chrome extension that automates form filling
      using AI text recognition and computer vision. Users can copy data from
      any source or upload document photos (including passports and IDs), and
      the tool automatically populates corresponding web form fields.</Text
    >
    <Heading level={2} size="xl" weight="semibold">Design Exploration</Heading>
    <Text class="mb-[1.562rem]"
      >Before designing the extension panel, I collected UI references and
      explored different visual directions, mainly on Dribbble and Pinterest. I
      also looked for similar tools in mobile apps but found nothing close to
      this use case.</Text
    >
  </ProjectContnetWrapper>
  <Image
    src={moodboardImg}
    alt="FillWise UI references moodboard"
    width="500"
    densities={[1, 2]}
    class="m-auto mb-[25px]"
  />
  <Text class="mb-[50px] max-w-[452px] m-auto text-center text-[15px] italic">
    UI references and visual directions collected before designing the
    extension panel.
  </Text>
  <ProjectContnetWrapper>
    <Heading level={2} size="xl" weight="semibold">Technical Approach</Heading>
    <Text class="mb-[1.562rem]"
      >Built initial prototype using AI tools for rapid validation, then
      collaborated with a developer to create a production-ready extension with
      robust browser integration and enhanced AI capabilities.</Text
    >
    <Heading level={2} size="xl" weight="semibold"
      >Iterating with Real Users</Heading
    >
    <Text class="mb-[1.562rem]"
      >I tested every version on my wife's real tasks and used her feedback.
      Later I started using the extension myself to apply for jobs. This is how
      Templates appeared: a template keeps your own data, like your email, and
      client data goes into the text area. My wife needed this too. For airline
      bookings she had to use her own email with each client's details, and now
      there is no extra switching between tabs or retyping.</Text
    >
  </ProjectContnetWrapper>
  <div class="mt-[60px] mb-[25px]">
    <SwiperSlider {sliderImages} initialWidth="270px" />
  </div>
  <Text class="mb-[50px] max-w-[452px] m-auto text-center text-[15px] italic">
    The panel went through several versions, from an early prototype to the
    current layout. One idea was tabs (the Pitch Deck concept) to fill a form
    exactly as in the source document or in a more free way. I didn't find a
    solution I liked and had more important tasks, so it stayed an idea.
  </Text>
  <ProjectContnetWrapper>
    <Heading level={2} size="xl" weight="semibold">Onboarding</Heading>
    <Text class="mb-[1.562rem]"
      >Chrome allows an extension to open a web page right after installation,
      so I used this moment for a guided onboarding. The user pins the
      extension and can try it right away on a built-in test form with prepared
      sample data (or their own). This way people see the core value before
      touching a real task.</Text
    >
  </ProjectContnetWrapper>
  <Image
    src={onboarding1Img}
    alt="FillWise onboarding, pin the extension"
    width="657"
    densities={[1, 2]}
    class="m-auto mb-[25px]"
  />
  <Image
    src={onboarding2Img}
    alt="FillWise onboarding, built-in test form with sample data"
    width="657"
    densities={[1, 2]}
    class="m-auto mb-[50px]"
  />
  <ProjectContnetWrapper>
    <Heading level={2} size="xl" weight="semibold">Feature Trade-offs</Heading>
    <Text class="mb-[1.562rem]"
      >The extension also works with PDFs and images: you can drop in your CV
      or a passport photo. I also built Excel autofill, but I had to put it
      aside. Google asks for wide access to user spreadsheets, which means
      touching sensitive client data, or I would have to pay $1000+ per year
      for extension verification. For a small side project that was not worth
      it. PDF form filling made it into production.</Text
    >
    <Heading level={2} size="xl" weight="semibold">Landing Page</Heading>
    <Text class="mb-[1.562rem]"
      >I made the first version of the current landing page with Figma AI,
      improved it by hand, then passed the design to Claude through the Figma
      MCP and shipped the result to production at <a
        href="https://fillwise.ai"
        target="_blank"
        rel="noopener"
        class="underline">fillwise.ai</a
      >.</Text
    >
  </ProjectContnetWrapper>
  <Image
    src={landingImg}
    alt="FillWise landing page"
    width="657"
    densities={[1, 2]}
    class="m-auto mb-[50px]"
  />
  <ProjectContnetWrapper>
    <Heading level={2} size="xl" weight="semibold">Business Impact</Heading>
    <Text>
      The extension has 200+ installs and several paying customers across HR
      and travel management sectors, reducing typical 10-minute form completion
      tasks to 30 seconds. Key use cases include passport data
      extraction for travel bookings and bulk passenger processing for group
      flights.
    </Text>
    <Text>
      TikTok marketing campaigns have increased product visibility, while user
      feedback drives continued feature development.</Text
    >
    <Text class="mb-[1.562rem]">
      Launched on Product Hunt to gain exposure and gather user insights - while
      it didn't generate significant traction, the experience provided valuable
      lessons in product positioning and community engagement.
    </Text>
    <Heading level={2} size="xl" weight="semibold"
      >What I Learned</Heading
    >
    <Text class="mb-[1.562rem]"
      >Building a useful product is not hard these days. Getting people to
      notice it is very hard. I tried LinkedIn ads, posted the project on
      Product Hunt and similar sites, started a TikTok with product videos, and
      worked on SEO. So far I haven't found a marketing channel that really
      works for FillWise, and I keep looking.</Text
    >
    <Heading level={2} size="xl" weight="semibold">What's Next</Heading>
    <Text
      >Soon FillWise will be free or almost free, and PDF filling will also
      work for documents without form fields inside.</Text
    >
  </ProjectContnetWrapper>
</Layout>
